    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1428"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/353.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 4, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have just received a telegram
                    from the Fathers of San Fernando Cathedral, San Antonio, Texas, informing me
                    that Bishop Segura and Father Vilalta, the last a Spanish subject, have been
                    imprisoned by the Constitutionalists at Tepic.</p>
                <p>I beg to call your attention to the matter and to request your good offices with
                    the Constitutionalists in order to obtain the release of these two priests.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
